<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Date:</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#000080; font-family:'Century Gothic'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Direct Line Group – Written evidence</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Draft Deregulation Bill</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Alan Bint</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> B.Sc. (Hons) ACII Chartered Insurer</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#000080; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Direct Line Group welcomes the opportunity to respond to the above Call for Evidence, published by the Department for Transport in July 2013.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Whilst Direct Line Group has no comment on the specific items mentioned in the Call for Evidence, we believe that there is an unintended consequence over the amendment to s.148 of the RTA.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">To illustrate, the below shows s.148 marked up with the proposed amendments:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt; page-break-after:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">148 Avoidance of certain exceptions to policies or securities.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">(1)Where a </span><span style="color:#808080; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:line-through">certificate of insurance or certificate of</span><span style="color:#808080; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">policy or </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">security</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:line-through"> </span><span style="color:#808080; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:line-through">has been delivered under section 147</span><span style="color:#808080; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">is issued or given for the purposes of this Part </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">of this </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Act</span><span style="color:#808080; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:line-through"> to the person by whom a policy has been effected or to whom a security has been given, so much of the policy or security</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">as purports to restrict— </span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">(a)the insurance of the persons insured by the policy, or </span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">(b)the operation of the security, </span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">(as the case may be) by reference to any of the matters mentioned in subsection (2) below shall, as respects such liabilities as are required to be covered by a policy under section 145 of this Act, be of no effect. </span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">(2)Those matters are— </span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">(a)the age or physical or mental condition of persons driving the vehicle, </span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">(b)the condition of the vehicle, </span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">(c)the number of persons that the vehicle carries, </span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">(d)the weight or physical characteristics of the goods that the vehicle carries, </span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">(e)the time at which or the areas within which the vehicle is used, </span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">(f)the horsepower or cylinder capacity or value of the vehicle, </span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">(g)the carrying on the vehicle of any particular apparatus, or </span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">(h)the carrying on the vehicle of any particular means of identification other than any means of identification required to be carried by or under the Vehicle Excise and Registration Act 1994.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">At present, this part of s.148 means insurers can't put the restrictions from (2)(a) to (2)(h) on the certificate (although they can feature elsewhere in the policy). Our interpretation of the above amendment may restrict our ability to include these restrictions in the policy (incl the schedule) too, although this is not clear. As the purpose of the above change is to remove the 'delivery' reference as opposed to making any other changes, we would suggest the following amendment:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">(1)Where a certificate of insurance or certificate of security has been </span><span style="color:#808080; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:line-through">delivered</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">issued or given for the purposes of this Part </span><span style="color:#808080; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:line-through">under section 147 </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">of this Act </span><span style="color:#808080; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:line-through">to the person by whom a policy has been effected or to whom a security has been given, so much of the policy or security </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">as purports to restrict...</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">P.64, schedule 3, section 3 of the Draft Deregulation Bill would need to be updated as follows:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">In section 148 (avoidance of certain exceptions to policies or securities), in subsection (1), for the words from "has been delivered" to "policy or security" substitute "has been issued or given for the purposes of this Part of this Act".</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:14.4pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Please let me know if you have any questions with regard to this or need any further information.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:14.4pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:14.4pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Given the nature of this submission being in respect of what we believe to be an incorrect amendment described in the draft form, we do not believe that it would be necessary to publish this submission.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:14.4pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:14.4pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">16 September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#000080; font-family:'Century Gothic'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>